Model Selection and Hyper-parameters

      • Model Choice: Regression models were used to analyze factors like age, gender, and wait times, providing insights into what drives patient satisfaction in the ER.

      • Predictive Power: These models help forecast satisfaction and identify areas for improvement, aligning with the projects goal of enhancing patient care.

      Tailored Hyper-parameters:

        • Optimization: Ridge and Lasso regularization were applied to prevent over-fitting, and hyper-parameters were fine-tuned to maximize accuracy.

          • Validation: Cross-validation ensured the models performed well across different patient data subsets.


          Model Development

          In this phase, models were trained using historical patient data to analyze trends in ER visits and satisfaction over time. The primary goal was to predict future patient? ?satisfaction and develop strategies to enhance the quality of care. By leveraging advanced regression techniques, valuable insights were obtained to inform proactive measures for improving patient experiences and operational efficiency in the ER.
